# Paper Mate environment file.
#
# Copy to `.env` (`cp .env.example .env`) and edit. Docker Compose auto-loads
# `.env` from the project root, so these values configure `docker compose up`
# with no extra flags. `.env` is gitignored. All values are optional and fall
# back to the defaults shown below; this file is the canonical list of knobs and
# grows as the project adds configuration.

# --- Storage ---
# Host directory for your library (mounted to /data inside the container, the
# AD-8 storage root). Defaults to the repo-root ./.paper-mate dir (tracked via
# .gitkeep, so it's pre-created on a fresh clone). Uncomment and set this to
# keep your papers/annotations somewhere else instead; pre-create the dir as
# your host user first (the container will not auto-create it).
# PAPER_MATE_DATA=${HOME}/.paper-mate

# --- Networking ---
# Host port the app is published on (the container always listens on 8000).
PAPER_MATE_PORT=8000

# --- Container identity ---
# Host user/group the container runs as, so files written under PAPER_MATE_DATA
# are owned by you (editable/deletable from the host, not root:root). Defaults
# to 1000:1000; override if your host uid/gid differ (check with `id -u` / `id -g`).
PAPER_MATE_UID=1000
PAPER_MATE_GID=1000

# --- Document structure ---
# How each imported paper is analyzed into headings/figures/tables (AD-13).
#   local  (default): the fast, deterministic, fully offline extractor.
#   hybrid          : the higher-fidelity Docling backend (bundled in the image;
#                     recovers section headings the local heuristic misses).
# Switching is just this value plus a container restart (docker compose up), no
# rebuild. Hybrid is slower per paper and its first pass may vary in the last
# decimal of coordinates (invisible on screen); local stays the offline default.
# PAPER_MATE_STRUCTURE_MODE=hybrid
#
# Hybrid device: "auto" (default) uses a GPU when the container is given one and
# falls back to CPU otherwise, so a GPU-less container still works. Force with
# "cpu" or "cuda".
# PAPER_MATE_STRUCTURE_HYBRID_DEVICE=auto
#
# Hybrid server URL. The default is in-container: the app launches the bundled
# hybrid server itself. Point this at a remote host to use an external sidecar
# instead, in which case nothing is launched in-container.
# PAPER_MATE_STRUCTURE_HYBRID_URL=http://localhost:5002
#
# To ACCELERATE hybrid with an NVIDIA GPU: install the NVIDIA Container Toolkit
# on the host, then uncomment the `deploy:` GPU block in docker-compose.yml. Left
# commented, hybrid runs on CPU (correct, just slower).
